-- Macquarie First's David Pleming Takes Sabbatical From South African Mining
-- Carli Lourens
-- 2010-06-29T08:45:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-29/macquarie-first-s-david-pleming-takes-sabbatical-from-south-african-mining.html

          
          
             Macquarie First South Securities
named  Kieran Daly  as head of mining research as chief general-
mining analyst  David Pleming  takes a six-month sabbatical from
Sept. 6.  
 Daly, 41, currently head of mining research at Investec
Securities, will have responsibility for diversified mining,
Johannesburg-based  Macquarie First South  said in a note.  
 Pleming, 51, was ranked top general-mining analyst in South
Africa in Johannesburg-based weekly magazine  Financial Mail ’s
annual survey of fund managers this year. Macquarie First South,
part of Australia’s Macquarie Group Ltd., was named the top-
ranked mining and commodities research firm in the survey.  
